ist Bookstore News, bookwomen changed people's lives and the world. In retelling their stories, Hogan not only shares the movement's tools with contemporary queer antiracist feminist activists and theorists, she gives us a vocabulary, strategy, and legacy for thinking through today's feminisms.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Nov 2020) 0aAnti-racismzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aFeminist literaturezUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aLesbian feminismzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aWomen's bookstoreszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 4aLambda Literary Awards. 4aLammy fnalist. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Women's Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311070808040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822374336zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822374336423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822374336.jpg  a978-3-11-070808-0  DUK Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles